CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 28, 1955, page 23, reads: "Champions All - Bowler from a large Eastern area were in Pittsburgh last week to help crown the various champions in YMCA Bowling League. In the top photo are members of the Woodpeckers team, 1954-55 league champions. Show being presented the team championship trophy by Bill Viggiana, assistant secretary of the Pittsburgh Ten Pin Bowling Association are, left to right: Psi Williams, Tom Alexander, Ollie Layne, Ted Page, John Humphreys and Pepper Davis. The Woodpeckers have won the crown three years running. In the other photo are members of the Centre Y. team, champions of the women's division. They are also being presented a trophy by Mr. Viggiana. From left to right are: Juanita Page, Louise Fulton, Louise Coleman, Myra Hannon and Ethel Bruce. This team also one the championship for the third year in a row. - Harris Photo"
TitMainTitle: Bill Viggiana presenting YMCA Bowling League championship trophy to Centre Y Team, from left: Juanita Page, Louise Fulton, Louise Coleman, Myra Davis Hannon, and Ethel Bruce, standing in bowling alley
